#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:63
msgid "### Backup methods"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:68
msgid ""
"**Complete**: one or more **filesystems** are backed up (kernel, data, "
"utilities, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:68
msgid ""
"**Partial**: one or more **files** are backed up (configurations, "
"directories, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:68
msgid ""
"**Differential**: only files modified since the last **complete** backup are "
"backed up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:68
msgid ""
"**Incremental**: only files modified since the last backup are backed up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:70
msgid "### Periodicity"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:73
msgid "**Pre-current** : at a given time (before a system update, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:73
msgid "**Periodic**: Daily, weekly, monthly, ..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    Before a system change, it can be useful to make a backup. However, there is no point in backing up data every day that is only changed every month.\n"
msgstr ""

