#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:205
msgid "#### Create a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:207
msgid "##### Create a backup in relative mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:209
msgid ""
"Creating a non-compressed backup in relative mode is done with the `cvf` "
"keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:213
msgid "``` tar c[vf] [device] [file(s)] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:219
msgid "``` [root]# tar cvf /backups/home.133.tar /home/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                                            |\n"
"|-----|--------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `c` | Creates a backup.                                      |\n"
"| `v` | Displays the name of the processed files.              |\n"
"| `f` | Allows you to specify the name of the backup (medium). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    The hyphen (`-`) in front of the `tar` keys is not necessary!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:231
msgid "##### Create a backup in absolute mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:233
msgid ""
"Creating a non-compressed backup explicitly in absolute mode is done with "
"the `cvfP` keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:237
msgid "``` $ tar c[vf]P [device] [file(s)] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:243
msgid "``` [root]# tar cvfP /backups/home.133.P.tar /home/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                       |\n"
"|-----|-----------------------------------|\n"
"| `P` |\tCreate a backup in absolute mode. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:251
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    With the `P` key, the path of the files to be backed up must be entered as **absolute**. If the two conditions (key `P` and path **absolute**) are not indicated, the backup is in relative mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:253
msgid "##### Creating a compressed backup with `gzip`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:255
msgid "Creating a compressed backup with `gzip` is done with the `cvfz` keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:259
msgid "``` $ tar cvzf backup.tar.gz dirname/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:263
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                      |\n"
"|-----|----------------------------------|\n"
"| `z` |\tCompresses the backup in _gzip_. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:267
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    The `.tgz` extension is an equivalent extension to `.tar.gz`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    Keeping the `cvf` (`tvf` or `xvf`) keys unchanged for all backup operations and simply adding the compression key to the end of the keys makes the command easier to understand (e.g. `cvfz` or `cvfj`, etc.).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:272
msgid "##### Creating a compressed backup with `bzip`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:274
msgid "Creating a compressed backup with `bzip` is done with the keys `cvfj`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:278
msgid "``` $ tar cvfj backup.tar.bz2 dirname/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:282
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                       |\n"
"|-----|-----------------------------------|\n"
"| `j` |\tCompresses the backup in _bzip2_. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    The `.tbz` and `.tb2` extensions are equivalent to `.tar.bz2` extensions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:287
msgid "##### Compression `compress`, `gzip`, `bzip2`, `lzip` and `xz`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:289
msgid ""
"Compression, and consequently decompression, will have an impact on resource "
"consumption (time and CPU usage)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:291
msgid ""
"Here is a ranking of the compression of a set of text files, from least to "
"most efficient:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:297
msgid ""
"- compress (`.tar.Z`)  - gzip (`.tar.gz`)  - bzip2 (`.tar.bz2`)  - lzip (`."
"tar.lz`)  - xz (`.tar.xz`)"
