#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:299
msgid "#### Add a file or directory to an existing backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:301
msgid "It is possible to add one or more items to an existing backup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:305
msgid "``` tar {r|A}[key(s)] [device] [file(s)] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:307
msgid "To add `/etc/passwd` to the backup `/backups/home.133.tar`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:311
msgid "``` [root]# tar rvf /backups/home.133.tar /etc/passwd ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:313
msgid ""
"Adding a directory is similar. Here add `dirtoadd` to `backup_name.tar`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:317
msgid "``` $ tar rvf backup_name.tar dirtoadd ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:322
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | Description                                                                      |\n"
"|-----|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `r` |\tAdds one or more files at the end of a direct access media backup (hard disk).   |\n"
"| `A` |\tAdds one or more files at the end of a backup on sequential access media (tape). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:325
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    It is not possible to add files or folders to a compressed backup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ tar rvfz backup.tgz filetoadd\n"
"    tar: Cannot update compressed archives\n"
"    Try `tar --help' or `tar --usage' for more information.\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    If the backup was performed in relative mode, add files in relative mode. If the backup was done in absolute mode, add files in absolute mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:336
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Mixing modes can cause problems when restoring.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:338
msgid "#### List the contents of a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:340
msgid "Viewing the contents of a backup without extracting it is possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:344
msgid "``` tar t[key(s)] [device] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key |\tDescription                                           |\n"
"|-----|-------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `t` |\tDisplays the content of a backup (compressed or not). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:356
msgid ""
"``` $ tar tvf backup.tar $ tar tvfz backup.tar.gz $ tar tvfj backup.tar.bz2 "
"```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:358
msgid ""
"When the number of files in a backup becomes large, it is possible to _pipe_ "
"the result of the `tar` command to a _pager_ (`more`, `less`, `most`, etc.):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:362
msgid "``` $ tar tvf backup.tar | less ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:365
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    To list or retrieve the contents of a backup, it is not necessary to mention the compression algorithm used when the backup was created. That is, a `tar tvf` is equivalent to `tar tvfj`, to read the contents, and a `tar xvf` is equivalent to `tar xvfj`, to extract.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:368
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    Always check the contents of a backup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:370
msgid "#### Check the integrity of a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:372
msgid ""
"The integrity of a backup can be tested with the `W` key at the time of its "
"creation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:376
msgid "``` $ tar cvfW file_name.tar dir/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:378
msgid ""
"The integrity of a backup can be tested with the key `d` after its creation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:382
msgid "``` $ tar vfd file_name.tar dir/ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:385
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    By adding a second `v` to the previous key, you will get the list of archived files as well as the differences between the archived files and those present in the file system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:396
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ tar vvfd  /tmp/quodlibet.tar .quodlibet/\n"
"    drwxr-x--- rockstar/rockstar     0 2021-05-21 00:11 .quodlibet/\n"
"    -rw-r--r-- rockstar/rockstar     0 2021-05-19 00:59 .quodlibet/queue\n"
"    [â¦]\n"
"    -rw------- rockstar/rockstar  3323 2021-05-21 00:11 .quodlibet/config\n"
"    .quodlibet/config: Mod time differs\n"
"    .quodlibet/config: Size differs\n"
"    [â¦]\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:398
msgid ""
"The `W` key is also used to compare the content of an archive against the "
"filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:407
msgid ""
"``` $ tar tvfW file_name.tar Verify 1/file1 1/file1: Mod time differs 1/"
"file1: Size differs Verify 1/file2 Verify 1/file3 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:409
msgid ""
"The verification with the `W` key cannot be done with a compressed archive. "
"The key `d` must be used:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:414
msgid "``` $ tar dfz file_name.tgz $ tar dfj file_name.tar.bz2 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:416
msgid "#### Extract (_untar_) a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:418
msgid "Extract (_untar]_) a ``*.tar`` backup is done with the `xvf` keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:420
msgid ""
"Extract the `etc/exports` file from the `/savings/etc.133.tar` backup into "
"the `etc` directory of the active directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:424
msgid "``` $ tar xvf /backups/etc.133.tar etc/exports ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:426
msgid ""
"Extract all files from the compressed backup `/backups/home.133.tar.bz2` "
"into the active directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:430
msgid "``` [root]# tar xvfj /backups/home.133.tar.bz2 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:432
msgid ""
"Extract all files from the backup `/backups/etc.133.P.tar` to their original "
"directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:436
msgid "``` $ tar xvfP /backups/etc.133.P.tar ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:439
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    Go to the right place.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:441
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Check the contents of the backup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:445
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key | \tDescription                                       |\n"
"|------|----------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `x`  |\tExtract files from the backup, compressed or not. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:448
msgid ""
"Extracting a _tar-gzipped_ (`*.tar.gz`) backup is done with the `xvfz` keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:452
msgid "``` $ tar xvfz backup.tar.gz ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:454
msgid ""
"Extracting a _tar-bzipped_ (`*.tar.bz2`) backup is done with the `xvfj` keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:458
msgid "``` $ tar xvfj backup.tar.bz2 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:461
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    To extract or list the contents of a backup, it is not necessary to mention the compression algorithm used to create the backup. That is, a `tar xvf` is equivalent to `tar xvfj`, to extract the contents, and a `tar tvf` is equivalent to `tar tvfj`, to list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:464
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    To restore the files in their original directory (key `P` of a `tar xvf`), you must have generated the backup with the absolute path. That is, with the `P` key of a `tar cvf`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:466
msgid "##### Extract only a file from a _tar_ backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:468
msgid ""
"To extract a specific file from a _tar_ backup, specify the name of that "
"file at the end of the `tar xvf` command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:472
msgid "``` $ tar xvf backup.tar /path/to/file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:474
msgid ""
"The previous command extracts only the `/path/to/file` file from the `backup."
"tar` backup. This file will be restored to the `/path/to/` directory "
"created, or already present, in the active directory."
