#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:511
msgid "## _CoPy Input Output_ - `cpio`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:513
msgid ""
"The `cpio` command allows saving on several successive media without "
"specifying any options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:518
msgid ""
"There is no option, unlike the `tar` command, to backup and compress at the "
"same time.  So it is done in two steps: backup and compression."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:520
msgid ""
"To perform a backup with `cpio`, you have to specify a list of files to "
"backup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:522
msgid "This list is provided with the commands `find`, `ls` or `cat`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:526
msgid "`find` : browse a tree, recursive or not;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:526
msgid "`ls` : list a directory, recursive or not;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:526
msgid "`cat` : reads a file containing the trees or files to be saved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:529
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    `ls` cannot be used with `-l` (details) or `-R` (recursive).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:531
#, no-wrap
msgid "    It requires a simple list of names.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:533
msgid "### Create a backup with `cpio` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:535
msgid "Syntax of the `cpio` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:539
msgid ""
"``` [files command |] cpio {-o| --create} [-options] [<file-list] [>device] "
"```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:543
msgid "With a redirection of the output of `cpio`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:547
msgid "``` $ find /etc | cpio -ov > /backups/etc.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:549
msgid "Using the name of a backup media :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:553
msgid "``` $ find /etc | cpio -ovF /backups/etc.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:555
msgid ""
"The result of the `find` command is sent as input to the `cpio` command via "
"a _pipe_ (character `|`, <kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>6</kbd>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:557
msgid ""
"Here, the `find /etc` command returns a list of files corresponding to the "
"contents of the `/etc` directory (recursively) to the `cpio` command, which "
"performs the backup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:559
msgid "Do not forget the `>` sign when saving or the `F save_name_cpio`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:564
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Options |\tDescription                                    |\n"
"| `-o`    |\tCreates a backup (_output_).                   |\n"
"| `-v`    |\tDisplays the name of the processed files.      |\n"
"| `-F`    |\tDesignates the backup to be modified (medium). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:566
msgid "Backup to a media :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:570
msgid "``` $ find /etc | cpio -ov > /dev/rmt0 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:572
msgid "The support can be of several types:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:575
msgid "tape drive: `/dev/rmt0` ;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:575
msgid "a partition: `/dev/sda5`, `/dev/hda5`, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:577
msgid "### Type of backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:579
msgid "#### Backup with relative path"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:584
msgid "``` $ cd / $ find etc | cpio -o > /backups/etc.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:586
msgid "#### Backup with absolute path"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:590
msgid "``` $ find /etc | cpio -o > /backups/etc.A.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:593
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    If the path specified in the `find` command is **absolute** then the backup will be performed in **absolute**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:595
#, no-wrap
msgid "    If the path indicated in the `find` command is **relative** then the backup will be done in **relative**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:597
msgid "### Add to a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:601
msgid ""
"``` [files command |] cpio {-o| --create} -A [-options] [<fic-list] {F|"
">device} ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:607
msgid "``` $ find /etc/shadow | cpio -o -AF SystemFiles.A.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:609
msgid "Adding files is only possible on direct access media."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:614
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                 |\n"
"|--------|---------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-A`   | Adds one or more files to a backup on disk. |\n"
"| `-F`   | Designates the backup to be modified.       |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:616
msgid "### Compressing a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:618
msgid "Save **then** compress"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:625
msgid ""
"``` $ find /etc | cpio âo > etc.A.cpio $ gzip /backups/etc.A.cpio $ ls /"
"backups/etc.A.cpio* /backups/etc.A.cpio.gz ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:627
msgid "Save **and** compress"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:631
msgid "``` $ find /etc | cpio âo | gzip > /backups/etc.A.cpio.gz ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:634
msgid ""
"There is no option, unlike the `tar` command, to save and compress at the "
"same time.  So it is done in two steps: saving and compressing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:636
msgid ""
"The syntax of the first method is easier to understand and remember, because "
"it is done in two steps."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:638
msgid ""
"For the first method, the backup file is automatically renamed by the `gzip` "
"utility which adds `.gz` to the end of the file name. Similarly the `bzip2` "
"utility automatically adds `.bz2`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:640
msgid "### Read the contents of a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:642
msgid "Syntax of the `cpio` command to read the contents of a _cpio_ backup:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:646
msgid "``` cpio -t [-options] [<fic-list] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:652
msgid "``` $ cpio -tv </backups/etc.152.cpio | less ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:657
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Options |\tDescription               |\n"
"|---------|---------------------------|\n"
"| `-t`    | Reads a backup.           |\n"
"| `-v`    | Displays file attributes. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:659
msgid ""
"After making a backup, you need to read its contents to be sure that there "
"were no errors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:661
msgid ""
"In the same way, before performing a restore, you must read the contents of "
"the backup that will be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:663
msgid "### Restore a backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:665
msgid "Syntax of the `cpio` command to restore a backup:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:669
msgid "``` cpio {-i| --extract} [-E file] [-options] [<device] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:675
msgid "``` $ cpio -iv </backups/etc.152.cpio | less ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:683
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Options                      | Description                                                         |\n"
"|------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-i`                         | Restore a complete backup.                                          |\n"
"| `-E file`                    | Restores only the files whose name is contained in file.            |\n"
"| `--make-directories` or `-d` | Rebuilds the missing tree structure.                                |\n"
"| `-u`                         | Replaces all files even if they exist.                              |\n"
"| `--no-absolute-filenames`    | Allows to restore a backup made in absolute mode in a relative way. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:686
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    By default, at the time of restoration, files on the disk whose last modification date is more recent or equal to the date of the backup are not restored (in order to avoid overwriting recent information with older information).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:688
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The `u` option, on the other hand, allows you to restore older versions of the files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:692
msgid "Absolute restoration of an absolute backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:696
msgid "``` $ cpio âivF home.A.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:698
msgid "Absolute restoration on an existing tree structure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:700
msgid ""
"The `u` option allows you to overwrite existing files at the location where "
"the restore takes place."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:704
msgid "``` $ cpio âiuvF home.A.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:706
msgid "Restore an absolute backup in relative mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:708
msgid ""
"The long option `no-absolute-filenames` allows a restoration in relative "
"mode. Indeed the `/` at the beginning of the path will be removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:712
msgid "``` $ cpio --no-absolute-filenames -divuF home.A.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:715
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    The creation of directories is perhaps necessary, hence the use of the `d` option\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:717
msgid "Restore a relative backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:721
msgid "``` $ cpio âiv <etc.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:723
msgid "Absolute restoration of a file or directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:725
msgid ""
"The restoration of a particular file or directory requires the creation of a "
"list file that must then be deleted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:731
msgid ""
"``` echo \"/etc/passwd\" > tmp cpio âiuE tmp -F etc.A.cpio rm -f tmp ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:733
msgid "## Compression - decompression utilities"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:735
msgid ""
"Using compression at the time of a backup can have a number of drawbacks:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:738
msgid "Lengthens the backup time as well as the restore time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:738
msgid "It makes it impossible to add files to the backup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:741
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    It is therefore better to make a backup and compress it than to compress it during the backup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:743
msgid "### Compressing with `gzip`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:745
msgid "The `gzip` command compresses data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:747
msgid "Syntax of the `gzip` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:751
msgid "``` gzip [options] [file ...] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:759
msgid "``` $ gzip usr.tar $ ls usr.tar.gz ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:761
msgid "The file receives the extension `.gz`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:763
msgid ""
"It keeps the same rights and the same last access and modification dates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:765
msgid "### Compressing with `bunzip2`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:767
msgid "The `bunzip2` command also compresses data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:769
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:817
msgid "Syntax of the `bzip2` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:773
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:821
msgid "``` bzip2 [options] [file ...] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:781
msgid "``` $ bzip2 usr.cpio $ ls usr.cpio.bz2 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:783
msgid "The file name is given the extension `.bz2`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:785
msgid ""
"Compression by `bzip2` is better than compression by `gzip` but it takes "
"longer to execute."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:787
msgid "### Decompressing with `gunzip`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:789
msgid "The `gunzip` command decompresses compressed data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:791
msgid "Syntax of the `gunzip` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:795
msgid "``` gunzip [options] [file ...] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:803
msgid "``` $ gunzip usr.tar.gz $ ls usr.tar ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:805
msgid ""
"The file name is truncated by `gunzip` and the extension `.gz` is removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:807
msgid "`gunzip` also decompresses files with the following extensions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:811
msgid "`.z` ;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:811
msgid "`-z` ;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:811
msgid "`_z` ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:813
msgid "### Decompressing with `bunzip2`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:815
msgid "The `bunzip2` command decompresses compressed data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:829
msgid "``` $ bunzip2 usr.cpio.bz2 $ ls usr.cpio ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:831
msgid ""
"The file name is truncated by `bunzip2` and the extension `.bz2` is removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:833
msgid "`bunzip2` also decompresses the file with the following extensions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:836
msgid "`-bz` ;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:836
msgid "`.tbz2` ;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/09-backups.md:836
msgid "`tbz` ."
msgstr ""
